<def f='linux-4.18.y/include/drm/drm_atomic.h' l='890' ll='895' type='bool drm_atomic_crtc_needs_modeset(const struct drm_crtc_state * state)'/>
<use f='linux-4.18.y/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_atomic.c' l='1739' u='c' c='drm_atomic_check_only'/>
<doc f='linux-4.18.y/include/drm/drm_atomic.h' l='871'>/**
 * drm_atomic_crtc_needs_modeset - compute combined modeset need
 * @state: &amp;drm_crtc_state for the CRTC
 *
 * To give drivers flexibility &amp;struct drm_crtc_state has 3 booleans to track
 * whether the state CRTC changed enough to need a full modeset cycle:
 * mode_changed, active_changed and connectors_changed. This helper simply
 * combines these three to compute the overall need for a modeset for @state.
 *
 * The atomic helper code sets these booleans, but drivers can and should
 * change them appropriately to accurately represent whether a modeset is
 * really needed. In general, drivers should avoid full modesets whenever
 * possible.
 *
 * For example if the CRTC mode has changed, and the hardware is able to enact
 * the requested mode change without going through a full modeset, the driver
 * should clear mode_changed in its &amp;drm_mode_config_funcs.atomic_check
 * implementation.
 */</doc>
